  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of trust by embezzling $25,000 from their employer, which warrants a period of incarceration to serve as both a punishment and a deterrent. However, the court must also consider significant mitigating factors. The defendant has no prior criminal record, indicating that this behavior is an aberration rather than a pattern. Furthermore, the defendant has already made proactive efforts to partially repay the stolen funds, showing remorse and a willingness to make the victim whole. Balancing the severity of the white-collar offense with the defendant's rehabilitative potential and restitution efforts, a short period of incarceration is appropriate. This will be followed by probation and a mandate to complete the remaining restitution.",
  "verdict": 6
}
